ğŸ› ï¸ Professional Analytics Workflow
1. Business Understanding
- Define the problem: What factors influence podium finishes, and how predictable are they?
- Identify stakeholders and their needs
- Establish success criteria (accuracy, interpretability, actionable insights)
2. Data Understanding
- Review dataset structure and metadata
- Assess data quality, completeness, and limitations
- Identify key entities: drivers, constructors, circuits, races, results
3. Data Preparation
- Clean and standardize fields
- Resolve inconsistent driver/team identifiers
- Engineer features such as:
- Driver experience
- Constructor performance indicators
- Circuit characteristics
- Qualifyingâ€‘toâ€‘race deltas
- Create an integrated analytical dataset
4. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Trend analysis (drivers, teams, circuits)
- Correlation analysis
- Distribution and variance checks
- Identification of key predictive variables
5. Modelling Approach
- Select an interpretable model (e.g., logistic regression or decision tree)
- Train/test split
- Evaluate performance using:
- Accuracy
- Precision/recall
- ROCâ€‘AUC
- Extract feature importance to support business insights
6. Insights & Recommendations
Translate analytical findings into stakeholderâ€‘ready insights, such as:
- Impact of qualifying position on podium probability
- Teamâ€‘specific performance patterns
- Circuitâ€‘level competitiveness
- Driver experience effects
7. Visualisation & Reporting
- Develop a dashboard (Power BI / Tableau) to present:
- Podium probability explorer
- Driver comparison tool
- Circuit insights
- Team performance trends
8. Conclusion & Next Steps
- Summarise key findings
- Highlight limitations
- Propose future enhancements (e.g., weather data, tyre strategy, safety car modelling)

